library(ggmap)
## Loading required package: ggplot2
## Google's Terms of Service: https://cloud.google.com/maps-platform/terms/.
## Please cite ggmap if you use it! See citation("ggmap") for details.
key <- readChar('../maps_key.txt', file.info('../maps_key.txt')$size)
register_google(key=key)
roadmap <- get_map("California", zoom = 6, source = "google", 
                      maptype = "roadmap")  # Using Google Maps.
## Source : https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=California&zoom=6&size=640x640&scale=2&maptype=roadmap&language=en-EN&key=xxx
## Source : https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json?address=California&key=xxx
toner_lite <- get_map("California", zoom = 6, source = "google", 
                       maptype = "toner-lite") # Using Stamen.
## maptype = "toner-lite" is only available with source = "stamen".
## resetting to source = "stamen"...
## Source : https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=California&zoom=6&size=640x640&scale=2&maptype=terrain&key=xxx
## Source : https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json?address=California&key=xxx
## Source : http://tile.stamen.com/toner-lite/6/9/23.png
